Suspicious!<br>
<br>
I'm sorry but you can't go buy a pair of jeans without being watched.  That's just how life is.  If you seriously don't like being watched then detatch completely from society because you will never escape it.  If stores didn't worry about theft then they'd loose several times the money they already do, and if the Government didn't keep an eye out for crime this nation <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>would be in Anarchy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Diablo sucked ass because of the cheating capabilities.  I praise SoE for making this game pretty much hack free.<br>
<br>
So we're all being watched to some degree or another, but seriously what does it matter to you?  There are so many things out there, like cheat programs, that SoE cares about, that they will completely dismiss anything else.  Sure, Microsofts gets a whole list of programs installed on your computer.  But what incentive do they have to single you out of hundreds of millions of computers to actually spend time and money in busting you.<br>
<br>
It's not the interns that have the freaking access to get to the ultra hidden IE hax0r paradise files on your hard drive.  And SoE isn't some jackass running this system from their basement.  It's a fully functional corporate system with security checks and balances and is already making a shitload of money and could care less about anything beyond getting your $13 a month.<br>
<br>
Baby steps you goons.  Baby steps to the internet.  Baby steps to understanding why being a part of a society entitles others to watch your actions.  Baby steps to understanding what they can and will do with the gobs of information it it would be if it was collected, and the 1 in a billion chance they screw you over for misinterpreting something running on your computer.  <br>
<br>
I bet any one of you would set up a security camera in your home if you suspected a baby sitter of stealing, or a camera on the street if someone was vandalizing your car regularly.  Yet you scream conspiracy when the government or SoE does it for the same reasons.<br>
<br>
I can't say SoE releases the most tested and thought over patches, but they have continually made some drastic improvements in this game.  If you think that's easy and can be accomplished bug free you're kidding yourself.  No one can criticise what SoE is doing with EverQuest until you've developed on a platform that large.  It's not as easy as you're trying to make it, not in the least.<br>
